==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suburbicary
<hw>Sub*ur"bi*ca*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>suburbicarius</ets>, equiv. to L. <ets>suburbanus</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>suburbicaire</ets>. See <er>Suburban</er>.]</ety> <def>Being in the
suburbs; -- applied to the six dioceses in the suburbs of Rome subject
to the pope as bishop of Rome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pope having stretched his authority beyond the bounds of his
<qex>suburbicarian</qex> precincts.</q> <rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suburethral</ent>⟦br⟧
